> It's one of those finicky situations where lots of things need to align just so; that's why I posted my reproducer, because it took me a long time to actually get it right.

@edsantiago perhaps you thought of this already, but ^^^ seems like great justification for copy-pasting the reproducer into a system test.  We did catch this at the integration-test level, but only by accident of timing.  Given how many engineer-hours went into fixing this, might serve us well to make double-damn sure this can't ever happen again :smile: 

Also, everyone here should give themselves a pat on the back:  We worked as a team and fixed an obscure bug before (as far as I'm aware) any users encountered it.  That's something to celebrate for sure.
